# A SURVEY FOUND THAT 65% OF ALL FINANCIAL CONSUMER WERE VERY SATISFIED WITH THEIR PRIMARY FINANCIAL INSTITUION. SUPPOSE THAT 25 FINANCIAL CONSUMERS ARE SAMPLED AND IF SURVEY RESULTS STILLS HOLDS TRUE TODAY, WHAT IS THE PROBABILTY THAT EXACTLY 19 ARE VERY SATISFIED WITH THEIR PRIMARY FINANCIAL INSTITUION.

# In[3]:


# There are two possiblity(SATISFIED AND NOT SATISFIED) so use of binomial
# p is the probability of success
# K 
# n is the number of samples
# pmf probability mass function
print(binom.pmf(k=19, n=25, p=0.65))


# According to US CENSUS BUREAU, APPROX 6% OF ALL WORKERS IN JACKSON, MISSISSIPPI ARE UNEMPLOYED. IN CONDUCTING THE RANDOM TELEPHONIC SURVEY IN JACKSON. WHAT IS THE PROBABILITY OF GETTNG TWO OR FEWER UNEMPLOYED WORKERS IN A SAMPLE OF 20?

# In[4]:


# FOR 1 AND FEWER WE ARE USING CDF FUNCTION (CUMLATIVE DIST FUCNTION)
binom.cdf(2,20,0.06)


