# WHAT IS THE PROBABILITY OF OBTAINING THE SCORE GREATER THAN 700 ON A GMAT TEST THAT HAS A MEAN OF 494 AND A STANDARD DEVIATION OF 100? ASSUME  GMAT SCORES ARE NORMALLY DISTRIBUTED.
# PROB(X>700|M = 494 AND SD = 100)?

# In[33]:


print(1-norm.cdf(700,494,100))


# FOR THE SAME GMAT SCORE EXAMINATION. WHAT IS THE PROBABILITY OF RANDOMLY DRAWING A SCORE THAT IS 550 OR LESS?

# In[34]:


print(norm.cdf(550,494,100))


# WHAT IS THE PROBABILTY OF GETTING A SCORE BETWEEN 350 AND 450 ON A SAME GMAT EXAM?

# In[35]:


print(norm.cdf(450,494,100)-norm.cdf(350,494,100))


